---
import Shell from '../layouts/Shell.astro';
import { eventsByCategory, formatDate, journal, performance, totalJournalEvents } from '../data/journal';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const recent = journal.slice(0, 7);
const scale = (value: number) => Math.max(8, Math.min(100, 18 + value * 220));
---

<Shell>
  <header class="topbar"><span>Research journal</span><a href="https://github.com/thedatadavis/extrapcap" aria-label="View source on GitHub">Source ↗</a></header>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Extrapolation Capital</h1>
    <p class="hero-copy">A paper-traded options research system studying how relative streaks, extrapolation bias, and mean reversion shape the next trade.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="dashboard-section" aria-labelledby="performance-title">
    <div class="section-heading"><div><h2 id="performance-title">Performance snapshot</h2><p>Latest research result based on modeled option prices</p></div><span class="data-note">Not a live result</span></div>
    <div class="metric-grid">
      <div class="metric"><span>Gain on capital at risk</span><strong>{(performance.returnOnCapital * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong><small>based on modeled prices</small></div>
      <div class="metric"><span>Average result per trade</span><strong>{(performance.expectancy * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong><small>modeled trades</small></div>
      <div class="metric"><span>Largest decline</span><strong>{(performance.maxDrawdown * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong><small>within this sample</small></div>
      <div class="metric"><span>Trades in sample</span><strong>{performance.trades}</strong><small>{performance.wins} wins · {performance.trades - performance.wins} losses</small></div>
    </div>
    <div class="chart-panel">
      <div class="chart-label"><span>Range of modeled trade results</span><span>Lower · middle · upper outcome</span></div>
      <div class="bar-chart" aria-label="Modeled trade-return quantiles"><i style={'height:' + scale(performance.quantiles.p05) + '%'}></i><i style={'height:' + scale(performance.quantiles.p50) + '%'}></i><i style={'height:' + scale(performance.quantiles.p95) + '%'}></i></div>
      <div class="chart-axis"><span>Lower outcome</span><span>Upper outcome</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lower-grid">
    <div class="journal-section"><div class="section-heading"><div><h2>Daily journal</h2><p>Decision records from the paper loop</p></div><a class="text-link" href={`${base}/journal/${recent[0]?.date}/`}>Read latest →</a></div>
      <div class="journal-list">{recent.map((entry) => <a class="journal-row" href={`${base}/journal/${entry.date}/`}><span class="journal-date">{formatDate(entry.date)}</span><span class="journal-title">The system recorded {entry.entries.length} journal event{entry.entries.length === 1 ? '' : 's'}</span><span class="arrow">→</span></a>)}</div>
    </div>
    <aside class="context-panel"><h2>About the system</h2><p>Extrapolation Capital is a paper-traded research system that studies whether a stock's recent run relative to the market can create a mean-reversion opportunity.</p><dl><div><dt>Journal events</dt><dd>{totalJournalEvents}</dd></div><div><dt>Operating mode</dt><dd>Paper only</dd></div><div><dt>Evidence</dt><dd>Modeled prices</dd></div></dl><a class="text-link" href="https://github.com/thedatadavis/extrapcap">Read the repository ↗</a></aside>
  </section>
  <footer class="page-footer">The displayed figures are modeled option proxies, not realized performance. Historical option-chain reconstruction remains a research dependency.</footer>
</Shell>
